title: Blue Origin Completes NS-23 Investigation, Releases Findings
summary: Blue Origin has completed and released its findings from the investigation of their NS-23 in flight anomaly and abort.

title: SpaceX keeping up cadence with Starlink Group 5-5 mission
summary: SpaceX’s 20th mission of the year is set to launch this Friday, March 24, sending another batch of Starlink satellites into low Earth orbit (LEO). The mission, named Starlink Group 5-5, is scheduled for liftoff at 11:43 AM EDT (15:43 UTC) from Space Launch Complex 40 (SLC-40) at Cape Canaveral Space Force Station, in Florida.

title: Dream Chaser is delayed again, raising questions about Vulcan launch plans
summary: Is there still a path to Vulcan flying a national security mission in 2023?

title: China loses UAE as partner for Chang’e-7 lunar south pole mission
summary: An agreement for a United Arab Emirates’ rover to fly on China’s Chang’e-7 lunar mission has apparently been hit by U.S. export control rules.

title: Advisory group backs European human spaceflight program using commercial approaches
summary: An advisory committee called on the European Space Agency to develop a comprehensive human spaceflight program using a more commercial approach.

title: Rocket Report: German launch company loses backer; Soyuz-5 may be in trouble
summary: “Shooting rockets off in the middle of Los Angeles or Dallas doesn’t make a lot of sense.”

title: Rocket Lab launches BlackSky sats, tests Electron ocean recovery
summary: After successfully conducting back-to-back flights from their recently-inaugurated US launch site, Rocket Lab returned to New Zealand for its second mission in March. Liftoff of “The Beat Goes On” mission took place on Friday, March 24 at 10:14 PM NZDT (09:14 UTC).

title: First crewed Starliner launch slips again
summary: The first flight of Boeing’s CST-100 Starliner commercial crew vehicle with astronauts on board, previously scheduled for late April, has been delayed, likely until the summer.

title: NASA warns of “devastating” impacts of potential budget cuts
summary: NASA Administrator Bill Nelson claims proposed spending reductions for fiscal year 2024 could have “devastating and potentially unrecoverable” effects on NASA programs, delaying or canceling many missions.

title: Boeing Starliner Crew Flight Test Delayed
summary: NASA has announced that Boeing Starliner's Crew Flight Test has officially been delayed.
